Enum NullBranchPath

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<NullBranchPath>
      • com.b2international.snowowl.core.api.NullBranchPath
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IBranchPath, Serializable, Comparable<NullBranchPath>

    public enum NullBranchPath
extends Enum<NullBranchPath>
implements IBranchPath
    Represents a *NON* existent branch path. Could be the parent of the MAIN top most branch in the hierarchy. Or could represent a not existing branch path.
    See Also:
    INSTANCE, IBranchPath

      • getOsPath

        public String getOsPath()
        Description copied from interface: IBranchPath
        Returns a string representation of this branch path which uses the platform-dependent path separator defined by File. This method is like IBranchPath.getPath() except that the latter always uses the same separator (IBranchPath.SEPARATOR) regardless of platform.

        This string is suitable for passing to File.File(String).

        Specified by:
        getOsPath in interface IBranchPath

      • lastSegment

        public String lastSegment()
        Description copied from interface: IBranchPath
        Returns with the last segment of the current branch path.

        If the branch path is: 

         MAIN∕VERSION_1∕TASK_300
        then this method returns with the following: 
         TASK_300
        This method never returns with null.
